The National Commission for Refugees, Migrants and Internally Displaced Persons (NCFRMI) has distributed relief items to the Internally Displaced Persons and other Persons of Concern (POCs) in Borno, Adamawa, Yobe and Taraba states. The commissioner of NCFRMI, Senator Basheer Garba Mohammed disclosed this in a statement signed by his special adviser on Media and Publicity, Sadiq Abdullateef in Abuja yesterday.  According to the statement, over 9,500 IDPs benefitted from Mayo Belwa, Michika, Madagali, Demsa, Numan and Lamorde camps in Adamawa state; over 5,000 IDPs from Bali camp in Taraba state and over 15,000 POCs from Geidam, Bade, Potiskum, Damaturu, Fika and Machina camps in Yobe state also benefitted from the gesture.  The commissioner, who was represented by the deputy director of human resources, Bello Muhammad Bello said the gesture was in line with the commission’s mandate of ensuring continuous welfare for persons of concern in the country.